Panel Data Regression Analysis (Crime-Weather Relationship)

Files:
1. panel_data
2. notebooks

Description
1. panel_data
	- contains five .csv files: ipc_data, crimes_against_women_data, cyber_data, property_data, violent_data
	- common variable description across .csv files:
				* s.no.: Serial No.
 				* districts: Districts in Tamil Nadu (32 districts as per 2011 division)
 					1. Ariyalur		17. Ramanathapuram
 					2. Chennai		18. Salem
 					3. Coimbatore		19. Sivaganga
 					4. Cuddalore		20. Thanjavur
 					5. Dharmapuri		21. The Nilgiris
 					6. Dindigul		22. Theni
 					7. Erode		23. Thiruvallur
 					8. Kancheepuram		24. Thiruvarur
 					9. Kanniyakumari	25. Thoothukudi
 					10. Karur		26. Tiruchirappalli
 					11. Krishnagiri		27. Tirunelveli
 					12. Madurai		28. Tiruppur
 					13. Nagappattinam	29. Tiruvannamalai
 					14. Namakkal		30. Vellore
 					15. Perambalur		31. Viluppuram
 					16. Pudukkottai		32. Virudunagar
 				* year: Years from 2011 to 2022
 				* pop_in_lak: Population of the district (in lakhs) in a year
 				* avg_temp: Average temperature of a district over a year (measured in celsius unit)
 				* tot_rf: Total rainfall of a district in a year (measured in millimeter unit)

	- ipc_data columns: s.no. districts, year, ipc_crimes, pop_in_lak, ipc_cr, avg_temp, tot_rf
		 	- variable description:
 				* ipc_crimes: Number of IPC crimes in a district in a year
  				* ipc_cr: IPC crime rate (IPC crimes per lakh population)

	- crimes_against_women_data columns: s.no., districts, year, type, crimes_against_women, pop_in_lak, craw_cr, avg_temp, tot_rf
 		 	- variable description:
 				* crimes_against_women: Number of crimes against women in a district in a year
 				* craw_cr: Crimes against women crime rate (Crimes against women per lakh population)

	- cyber_data columns: s.no., districts, year, type, cyber_crime, pop_in_lak, cyber_cr, avg_temp, tot_rf
 		 	- variable description:
 				* cyber_crimes: Number of cyber crimesin a district in a year
 				* cyber_cr: Cyber crime rate (Cyber crimes per lakh population)

	- property_data columns: s.no., districts, year, type, property_crimes, pop_in_lak, property_cr, avg_temp, tot_rf
 		 	- variable description:
 				* property_crimes: Number of property crimes in a district in a year
 				* property_cr: Property crime rate (Property crimes per lakh population)

	- violent_data columns:  s.no., districts, year, type, violent_crimes, pop_in_lak, violent_cr, avg_temp, tot_rf
 		 	- variable description:
 				* violent_crimes: Number of violent crimes in a district in a year
 				* craw_cr: Violent crime rate (Violent crimes per lakh population)
2. notebooks
	- contains the python code for analysis in Jupyter Notebooks
	- dependent variable: crime rate (ipc_cr, craw_cr, cyber_cr, property_cr, violent_cr); independent variables: temperature (avg_temp) and rainfall (tot_rf)
	- analysis process:
		- Model estimation (models: Pooled OLS, Fixed Effects, Random Effects)
		- Model selection: F-test for Pooled OLS vs. FE; Hausman test for FE vs RE
		- Model validity/diagnostic checks: Test for heteroskedasticity, serial correlation, cross-section dependency
		- Model re-estimation: Estimated model checked for residuals and normality
3. output
	- contains output files of the analysis for each category
		- IPCPanelDataAnalysis: output for overall IPC crimes category
		- CRAWPanelDataAnalysis: output for crimes against women category
		- CyberPanelDataAnalysis: output for cyber crime category
		- PropertyPanelDataAnalysis: output for property crime category
		- ViolentPanelDataAnalysis: output for violent crime category
